14/01/2008
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Further search operations for eight Bulgarian sailors who disappeared in a cargo shipwreck in the Azov Sea would be futile in the icy waters of the area, Ukraine's Emergency Situations Ministry said on Sunday (January 13th).
The Vanessa, sailing under a Bulgarian flag, sank on the night of January 3rd with 11 people onboard.
One person survived the accident and two bodies have been recovered.
Bulgaria is investigating the reasons for the incident and is considering six possible scenarios, including business interests and incorrectly stowed and secured cargo.
(Sofia news agency, Netinfo - 14/01/08;
BGNES, ITAR-TASS, BNT - 13/01/07)
